<section id="using-vm-server" xreflabel="Installing a VM Server">
	<title>Installing a VM Server</title>

<para>
A VM Server is machine that can house virtual frontend appliances.
It is required to build a VM Server if you wish to build virtual clusters.
</para>

<para>
Building a VM Server is just like building a traditional frontend, except
that you <emphasis>must supply the Xen Roll during the frontend
installation</emphasis>.
Follow the procedure
<ulink url="/roll-documentation/base/&document-version;/install-frontend.html">
Install and Configure Your Frontend</ulink> and be sure to supply the Xen Roll.
</para>

<para>
After you build the VM Server, you'll need to install VM Containers (see
the next section).
</para>

</section>

